50|$|In 1960, {{the local}} signal boxes {{began to be}} {{replaced}} by an <b>automatic</b> <b>block</b> <b>signaling</b> system. The first line to be modernised was from Mannheim to Seckenheim. In 1967, the Schriesheim-Handschuhsheim section was resignalled. In 1969, the whole line from Weinheim to Heidelberg was resignalled. By the end of the 1980s the entire route network had been equipped with <b>automatic</b> <b>block</b> <b>signaling.</b> Today, the lines are controlled by three signal boxes in Edingen, Schriesheim and Käfertal.|$|R
