5000|$|Robinson began {{developing}} an <b>automatic</b> <b>block</b> <b>signal</b> system for railroads in 1867. His first system was {{installed on the}} Philadelphia and Erie Railroad in 1870. He received multiple patents for railway signaling inventions: ...|$|E
50|$|The line is not {{equipped}} with {{centralized traffic control}} or <b>automatic</b> <b>block</b> <b>signalling.</b> It is dispatched via radio under the track warrant control rules.|$|R
